Questions:
What should you do if you decide to withdraw from the TOPS for African American Breast Cancer Survivors study?
A) Continue to attend the study visits for measurements without participating in other activities;
B) Contact Dr. Nia S. Mitchell in writing to inform her of your decision to withdraw;
C) Pay back any compensation you have received for participating in the study;
D) Immediately stop using the digital scale provided by the study.

Correct answer: B) Contact Dr. Nia S. Mitchell in writing to inform her of your decision to withdraw.
